Description: Body sherd of Attic black-figured pottery Corinthian type skyphos; interior glazed black; exterior: black-figure decoration consisting of shoulder and neck, in added red, of feline, probably a panther, to right; at right, two incised spoked rosettes with red hearts with incision.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.0340) (Phase 1)
